McDermott International Inc saidthe purchase of a 5.4 pct block of its stock was an apparentviolation of the laws of Panama, its country of incorporation.    The company said a detailed disclosure of an acquisitionoffer must be made to the Panamanian National SecuritiesCommission or to the target's board before acquiring more thanfive pct stake.    It said transfers of securities in violation of thesePanamanian regulations are invalid.    The company was not immediately available to say who hadacquired the 5.4 pct block of stock. Reuter&#3;